1
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:37,440
=Have a Crush on You=

2
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:41,381 --> 00:01:42,862
Ding, get ready.

4
00:01:43,261 --> 00:01:44,142
We'll head to
the Outpatient Department later.

5
00:01:44,341 --> 00:01:45,182
Okay, Mr. Qian.

6
00:01:45,701 --> 00:01:46,581
Wu,

7
00:01:46,661 --> 00:01:47,701
how many surgeries do we have today?

8
00:01:47,701 --> 00:01:48,422
Two.

9
00:01:48,581 --> 00:01:49,581
Join me for the surgeries later.

10
00:01:49,581 --> 00:01:50,661
Yes, Mr. Ning.

11
00:01:51,102 --> 00:01:51,782
What about me?

12
00:01:53,542 --> 00:01:54,581
I'll talk to you

13
00:01:54,621 --> 00:01:56,021
once I'm done with the surgeries.

14
00:02:04,062 --> 00:02:05,062
Dr. Ruan,

15
00:02:05,261 --> 00:02:05,822
come here for a second.

16
00:02:06,142 --> 00:02:06,502
Yes, sir.

17
00:02:10,222 --> 00:02:11,261
Get me some water.

18
00:02:15,022 --> 00:02:15,901
Mr. Ning,

19
00:02:15,901 --> 00:02:17,701
I'll follow Mr. Qian
to the Outpatient Department now.

20
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:24,062
Mr. Ning,

21
00:02:24,181 --> 00:02:25,541
what are my tasks for today?

22
00:02:25,621 --> 00:02:27,222
Translate this neurosurgery thesis.

23
00:02:28,181 --> 00:02:29,062
And, type these medical histories

24
00:02:29,782 --> 00:02:30,862
into the computer.

25
00:02:33,621 --> 00:02:34,942
Bring the medical consumables required
on Wednesday

26
00:02:34,942 --> 00:02:36,142
to the material room.

27
00:02:36,942 --> 00:02:37,662
Wu, let's go.

28
00:02:37,862 --> 00:02:38,261
Okay.

29
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:07,780
(Material Box)

30
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:14,780
(Material Box)

31
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:19,140
(Beiya Hospital, Outstanding Medical
Services, Meticulous Care)

32
00:03:23,101 --> 00:03:23,981
Dr. Ning.

33
00:03:25,862 --> 00:03:27,261
Why did you follow me here?

34
00:03:28,821 --> 00:03:30,422
You said my brain was fine.

35
00:03:30,422 --> 00:03:31,621
What did you mean by that?

36
00:03:32,382 --> 00:03:34,142
Didn't I explain it to you already?

37
00:03:34,181 --> 00:03:34,981
Judging from the images

38
00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:35,981
produced by the CT scan,

39
00:03:35,981 --> 00:03:37,901
your brain is perfectly fine.

40
00:03:38,302 --> 00:03:40,662
If so, why can't I sleep?

41
00:03:40,901 --> 00:03:42,541
I couldn't sleep no matter what.

42
00:03:43,222 --> 00:03:45,341
It's definitely not related
to your brain.

43
00:03:45,862 --> 00:03:46,621
In the future,

44
00:03:46,621 --> 00:03:48,261
you should head to the
Outpatient Department for a diagnosis

45
00:03:48,302 --> 00:03:49,302
instead of the washroom.

46
00:03:54,261 --> 00:03:55,502
Dr. Ning,

47
00:03:55,541 --> 00:03:56,701
I didn't mean to offend you.

48
00:03:56,701 --> 00:03:57,502
Dr. Ning.

49
00:03:58,101 --> 00:03:59,541
I've already explained it to you.

50
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:00,382
You're not sick.

51
00:04:00,382 --> 00:04:02,302
Dr. Ning, I'm sick.

52
00:04:02,662 --> 00:04:04,181
This is the doctor's office.

53
00:04:04,181 --> 00:04:05,101
Do not follow me inside.

54
00:04:05,101 --> 00:04:06,382
I can't sleep every night!

55
00:04:06,382 --> 00:04:08,142
It feels terrible!

56
00:04:08,461 --> 00:04:09,382
Dr. Ning!

57
00:04:10,502 --> 00:04:11,782
What's the matter? Do you need anything?

58
00:04:12,942 --> 00:04:13,782
Are you a doctor?

59
00:04:14,502 --> 00:04:15,741
Are you a neurosurgeon too?

60
00:04:16,502 --> 00:04:17,262
That's right.

61
00:04:19,181 --> 00:04:21,021
Please take a look at this for me.

62
00:04:21,062 --> 00:04:22,982
Please tell me if I'm sick or not.

63
00:04:31,141 --> 00:04:32,702
What do you think? Am I sick?

64
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:36,062
Judging from the images,

65
00:04:36,062 --> 00:04:37,461
you look fine.

66
00:04:37,461 --> 00:04:39,062
If so, why do I suffer from insomnia
every night?

67
00:04:39,062 --> 00:04:40,062
I suffer from headaches too.

68
00:04:40,102 --> 00:04:41,461
Sometimes, I even feel like puking.

69
00:04:41,542 --> 00:04:43,141
When I searched for my symptoms online,

70
00:04:43,262 --> 00:04:44,901
it said that I had a brain tumor.

71
00:04:47,542 --> 00:04:48,421
Have you asked Mr. Ning about
your condition?

72
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:49,262
What did he say?

73
00:04:49,262 --> 00:04:50,062
He said I'm fine.

74
00:04:50,102 --> 00:04:51,301
He didn't give me any medicine too.

75
00:04:51,382 --> 00:04:53,181
He's one of the best in our field.

76
00:04:53,181 --> 00:04:55,382
You're not sick when he says you're not.

77
00:04:55,542 --> 00:04:56,861
Shouldn't you be relieved to hear that?

78
00:04:56,861 --> 00:04:58,301
Even so, he can at least
give me some medicine.

79
00:04:58,301 --> 00:04:59,502
I can't sleep right now.

80
00:05:03,861 --> 00:05:04,662
Hello, Mr. Ning.

81
00:05:09,262 --> 00:05:09,741
Mr. Ning,

82
00:05:10,222 --> 00:05:12,102
please review
this case for me.

83
00:05:12,621 --> 00:05:13,102
Coming.

84
00:05:20,062 --> 00:05:21,181
Mr. Ning, here.

85
00:05:22,662 --> 00:05:23,861
I don't understand this part.

86
00:05:24,502 --> 00:05:25,502
Place this case history

87
00:05:25,502 --> 00:05:27,222
and the X-ray film at my table later.

88
00:05:27,222 --> 00:05:28,021
Okay.

89
00:05:29,021 --> 00:05:30,341
Organize this report for me.

90
00:05:41,822 --> 00:05:42,461
I think you're suffering

91
00:05:42,461 --> 00:05:44,222
from insomnia because of your troubles.

92
00:05:44,222 --> 00:05:45,861
Have you encountered
any stressful events lately?

93
00:05:46,581 --> 00:05:47,861
My wife wants to get a divorce.

94
00:05:48,141 --> 00:05:49,461
My son will be attending
high school soon.

95
00:05:49,621 --> 00:05:51,581
And, my dog gave birth to seven puppies.

96
00:05:52,222 --> 00:05:53,102
Our neighbor came to borrow
vinegar

97
00:05:53,141 --> 00:05:54,181
for the dumplings.

98
00:05:54,502 --> 00:05:56,021
Even now, he hasn't returned it to me.

99
00:05:56,062 --> 00:05:57,222
I've been fretting about them

100
00:05:57,222 --> 00:05:58,542
all day long.

101
00:05:58,542 --> 00:06:00,141
- I can't stop thinking about them.
- Hello, Mr. Ning?

102
00:06:00,181 --> 00:06:01,102
Come to my office.

103
00:06:01,102 --> 00:06:02,062
I need to talk to you.

104
00:06:02,421 --> 00:06:03,222
Alright, I'll head upstairs now.

105
00:06:03,222 --> 00:06:04,702
Doctor, can you give me some medicine?

106
00:06:05,181 --> 00:06:06,382
Can you please give me some medicine?

107
00:06:06,421 --> 00:06:07,581
I'm sorry. I have to go.

108
00:06:07,581 --> 00:06:08,461
I'll head upstairs first.

109
00:06:08,502 --> 00:06:09,102
Doctor,

110
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:10,741
can I not
look for Dr. Ning in the future?

111
00:06:10,782 --> 00:06:12,102
Can I look for you instead?

112
00:06:12,301 --> 00:06:13,702
You can look for me anytime
if you have any questions.

113
00:06:14,062 --> 00:06:14,542
Okay.

114
00:06:15,181 --> 00:06:16,102
It's not a big deal.

115
00:06:16,102 --> 00:06:17,782
Communicate with your wife more often

116
00:06:17,782 --> 00:06:19,102
and try to resolve
the misunderstandings.

117
00:06:19,141 --> 00:06:20,581
And, try to avoid taking sleeping pills.

118
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:22,621
There's a side effect to it,
and you'll become dependent on it.

119
00:06:23,021 --> 00:06:24,062
May you sleep well tonight.

120
00:06:24,062 --> 00:06:25,222
Thank you, Dr. Ruan.

121
00:06:25,222 --> 00:06:26,102
You're truly a nice person.

122
00:06:26,141 --> 00:06:26,901
Dr. Ruan.

123
00:06:33,621 --> 00:06:35,382
Mr. Ning, were you looking for me?

124
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:37,102
What were you doing out there?

125
00:06:39,301 --> 00:06:40,861
I encountered a troubled patient.

126
00:06:40,861 --> 00:06:41,982
I was free anyway.

127
00:06:42,542 --> 00:06:43,502
I had a chat with him.

128
00:06:44,181 --> 00:06:45,461
Have you finished moving
all the medical consumables?

129
00:06:45,502 --> 00:06:46,181
I have.

130
00:06:46,181 --> 00:06:47,181
Have you translated the thesis?

131
00:06:48,861 --> 00:06:49,861
I've sent it to your mailbox.

132
00:06:49,861 --> 00:06:50,782
Please check it.

133
00:07:01,581 --> 00:07:03,861
Where did you learn your
English for Medicine?

134
00:07:03,942 --> 00:07:04,982
Did you even pass the subject?

135
00:07:06,702 --> 00:07:07,702
I got 85 points.

136
00:07:07,702 --> 00:07:08,662
I was the third in class.

137
00:07:09,062 --> 00:07:12,181
Objective to surgery, neuronavigation.

138
00:07:12,222 --> 00:07:14,102
It should be the neuronavigation system.

139
00:07:14,102 --> 00:07:14,901
You knew the term, right?

140
00:07:14,901 --> 00:07:16,021
Why did you ask me to translate it then?

141
00:07:16,062 --> 00:07:17,262
I was afraid that
you might not understand.

142
00:07:18,222 --> 00:07:19,662
How's the progress
with the medical histories?

143
00:07:20,702 --> 00:07:21,662
I haven't finished them yet.

144
00:07:21,782 --> 00:07:23,621
How dare you chat with a patient then?

145
00:07:23,621 --> 00:07:24,782
Do you take yourself as a priestess now?

146
00:07:26,581 --> 00:07:28,382
He was emotionally affected.

147
00:07:29,262 --> 00:07:29,982
Remember this.

148
00:07:29,982 --> 00:07:31,421
Doctors are only
responsible for giving diagnoses,

149
00:07:31,421 --> 00:07:32,581
not counseling sessions.

150
00:07:36,382 --> 00:07:37,341
Mr. Ning,

151
00:07:37,621 --> 00:07:38,822
sometimes, I think the patients

152
00:07:38,822 --> 00:07:39,621
just want us

153
00:07:39,621 --> 00:07:40,901
to comfort them.

154
00:07:40,901 --> 00:07:42,621
He followed you all the way
to the restroom.

155
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,062
Can't you just tell him something nice?

156
00:07:46,262 --> 00:07:46,861
Great timing.

157
00:07:46,901 --> 00:07:48,341
Both of the newcomers are here.

158
00:07:48,341 --> 00:07:49,421
I'll emphasize this again.

159
00:07:49,421 --> 00:07:51,581
Remember not to
be too close with your patients.

160
00:07:51,621 --> 00:07:52,421
But why?

161
00:07:52,461 --> 00:07:54,021
So you can work better.

162
00:07:54,662 --> 00:07:55,621
Mr. Ning,

163
00:07:55,621 --> 00:07:57,421
I think you're putting me
on the spot here.

164
00:07:57,542 --> 00:07:58,942
I have to move so many things.

165
00:07:58,982 --> 00:07:59,861
And, I have to translate a thesis.

166
00:07:59,861 --> 00:08:01,062
I don't have time
for the medical histories.

167
00:08:01,062 --> 00:08:02,262
How many medical histories
have you recorded?

168
00:08:03,102 --> 00:08:04,062
One-third of them.

169
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:12,420
(Beiya Hospital)

170
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:13,840
(Delayed Intracranial Hematoma)

171
00:08:13,861 --> 00:08:15,262
This is delayed intracranial hematoma,

172
00:08:15,262 --> 00:08:16,861
one of the medical histories
you recorded.

173
00:08:16,901 --> 00:08:17,822
Tell me

174
00:08:17,822 --> 00:08:20,581
the reason and the process
of the onset.

175
00:08:23,382 --> 00:08:24,461
After the patient's brain was damaged,

176
00:08:24,461 --> 00:08:25,741
no hematoma was detected

177
00:08:25,741 --> 00:08:26,461
after the first CT scan.

178
00:08:26,621 --> 00:08:28,141
Did you even understand my question?

179
00:08:30,662 --> 00:08:31,301
Dr. Ruan, I hope you can

180
00:08:31,782 --> 00:08:33,541
bring your brain to work next time.

181
00:08:34,022 --> 00:08:35,101
I need an assistant,

182
00:08:35,101 --> 00:08:36,262
not a typewriter.

183
00:08:36,502 --> 00:08:38,301
As an inexperienced neurosurgeon,

184
00:08:38,661 --> 00:08:40,702
the tasks you're doing have their
own meanings to them.

185
00:08:41,462 --> 00:08:42,181
Understood?

186
00:08:49,502 --> 00:08:51,541
Don't put on so much lipstick
in the hospital.

187
00:08:53,902 --> 00:08:54,702
Everyone, listen up.

188
00:08:54,702 --> 00:08:55,741
From tomorrow onward,

189
00:08:55,741 --> 00:08:56,781
Dr. Ruan alone will be in charge

190
00:08:56,781 --> 00:08:58,022
of moving the medical consumables.

191
00:08:58,382 --> 00:08:58,981
Got it.

192
00:09:08,582 --> 00:09:10,621
Now, we'll summarize the performance
of our residents

193
00:09:10,621 --> 00:09:13,181
and medical interns.

194
00:09:13,462 --> 00:09:16,262
Let's talk about Dr. Ding, a resident.

195
00:09:17,062 --> 00:09:19,262
For the past month,

196
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:20,981
not only can Dr. Ding Yiyuan
assist the chief physician

197
00:09:20,981 --> 00:09:22,342
to complete his outpatient duty,

198
00:09:22,582 --> 00:09:25,181
but she's also the head assistant
for five surgeries.

199
00:09:25,262 --> 00:09:26,661
She performed well.

200
00:09:26,822 --> 00:09:27,541
Give her a big hand.

201
00:09:28,221 --> 00:09:29,342
Do not get ahead of yourself.

202
00:09:29,342 --> 00:09:30,301
Thank you, Mr. Qian.

203
00:09:30,342 --> 00:09:32,582
Let's talk about Dr. Ruan.

204
00:09:33,621 --> 00:09:34,902
Outpatient duty,

205
00:09:36,262 --> 00:09:37,022
none.

206
00:09:38,462 --> 00:09:39,502
Surgery duty,

207
00:09:40,981 --> 00:09:41,741
none.

208
00:09:49,902 --> 00:09:50,702
Dr. Ruan,

209
00:09:51,421 --> 00:09:54,421
although there's a difference
between you and Dr. Ding,

210
00:09:54,421 --> 00:09:55,541
I believe that you can

211
00:09:55,781 --> 00:09:57,462
definitely catch up to her.

212
00:09:59,702 --> 00:10:00,462
Alright!

213
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:02,462
Let's keep up the good work.

214
00:10:02,621 --> 00:10:03,582
Time to go on our rounds.

215
00:10:03,861 --> 00:10:04,621
Let's go.

216
00:10:14,621 --> 00:10:15,861
How are you? Do you
feel uncomfortable anywhere?

217
00:10:15,861 --> 00:10:16,661
No.

218
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:18,582
How's your appetite?

219
00:10:18,621 --> 00:10:19,462
It's fine.

220
00:10:19,502 --> 00:10:20,421
What about your body temperature?

221
00:10:20,502 --> 00:10:21,382
It's normal.

222
00:10:22,221 --> 00:10:22,942
Modify the antibiotic

223
00:10:22,942 --> 00:10:23,861
according to her allergies.

224
00:10:24,981 --> 00:10:26,661
You must take note not to let him

225
00:10:26,661 --> 00:10:28,621
exert too much strength during
the excretion process.

226
00:10:29,062 --> 00:10:30,342
How long has he been sleeping?

227
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:31,462
It's been quite some time.

228
00:10:32,822 --> 00:10:33,181
Arrange a head

229
00:10:33,181 --> 00:10:34,142
and chest CT scan for him.

230
00:10:34,142 --> 00:10:35,502
Change the Mannitol dosage
to 250ml,

231
00:10:35,502 --> 00:10:36,462
q12h.

232
00:10:36,781 --> 00:10:37,181
Alright.

233
00:10:42,342 --> 00:10:43,462
Did you jot it down?

234
00:10:51,382 --> 00:10:53,382
Mr. Ning, we need to do a ward handover.

235
00:10:53,382 --> 00:10:54,382
Alright, I'll be there soon.

236
00:10:54,382 --> 00:10:55,342
You can go ahead.

237
00:11:01,301 --> 00:11:03,221
Mr. Ning, can I get off work now?

238
00:11:03,741 --> 00:11:04,781
Ask Dr. Qian.

239
00:11:04,781 --> 00:11:05,661
Don't ask me.

240
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:47,900
(Beiya Hospital)

241
00:11:58,462 --> 00:11:59,781
Get in. I'll send you home.

242
00:11:59,981 --> 00:12:01,781
It's fine. I can take the subway.

243
00:12:01,981 --> 00:12:03,101
I need to speak with you.

244
00:12:18,382 --> 00:12:19,822
What's with the long face?

245
00:12:19,861 --> 00:12:21,101
Are you going to continue your lecture?

246
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:24,421
We've been together for quite some time.

247
00:12:24,741 --> 00:12:26,181
You should know the things I like

248
00:12:26,181 --> 00:12:27,342
and the things I don't.

249
00:12:27,382 --> 00:12:28,702
Don't buy braised meat and

250
00:12:28,702 --> 00:12:29,421
sweet and sour pork ribs
for me in the future.

251
00:12:29,421 --> 00:12:30,142
I don't like sweet food.

252
00:12:30,142 --> 00:12:31,142
I didn't buy them for you.

253
00:12:31,142 --> 00:12:32,342
Take note of it next time.

254
00:12:35,981 --> 00:12:38,022
When can I perform outpatient duty
and surgeries?

255
00:12:38,221 --> 00:12:39,822
When I think you're ready.

256
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:41,661
I've reviewed your suture techniques

257
00:12:41,702 --> 00:12:42,541
during the last surgery.

258
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:43,661
You need more practice.

259
00:12:44,301 --> 00:12:45,861
It's because I didn't
perform well last time.

260
00:12:48,181 --> 00:12:49,541
Why didn't you perform well?

261
00:12:49,741 --> 00:12:51,181
I was a little nervous.

262
00:12:52,142 --> 00:12:53,142
Why were you nervous then?

263
00:12:53,142 --> 00:12:54,342
Because you were beside me.

264
00:12:55,342 --> 00:12:56,101
Why were you thinking about me

265
00:12:56,101 --> 00:12:57,062
instead of focusing on your work?

266
00:12:57,062 --> 00:12:58,142
Who said I was thinking about you?

267
00:12:58,142 --> 00:12:59,462
Stop looking for excuses.

268
00:12:59,462 --> 00:13:01,022
Do you know what you're doing?

269
00:13:02,062 --> 00:13:04,142
You're blaming others
for your own mistake here.

270
00:13:04,421 --> 00:13:05,942
Yeah, you're the mistake here.

271
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:20,181
What?

272
00:13:20,621 --> 00:13:22,022
Move out of the way.
I need to take my stuff.

273
00:13:28,262 --> 00:13:29,301
Have you turned into a child again?

274
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:30,822
You're actually taking
children's crackers?

